 anglo energy ltd former amex symbol ael and currently based in hamilton bermuda is an sp  oil natural gas and geothermal drilling contractor operating on land throughout the americas the middle east the far east and africa it also performs onshore wellservicing in north america and provides rigs for offshore oil platform workover and also for offshore drilling rig servicing the company provides many support services for both offshore and onshore oil drilling and for wellservicing operations the company has a charter fleet of  marine vessels for offshore operations it also makes top drilling drives directional drilling systems equipment for rig instrumentation and for data collection equipment for drill pipe handling and software for rig reporting as of  the company owned  land workover and wellservicing rigs in the united states and  rigs in canada as well as  oil platform rigs  jackup barge rigs and  barge rigs its former chief executive officer eugene m isenberg graduated in  from the university of massachusetts amherst and the schools isenberg school of management is named in his honor contents  history  anglo energy  nabors industries  ethics committee investigation  golden coffin controversy  jet abuse investigation  corporate affairs  see also  references  external links historyedit anglo energyedit anglo energy ltd was founded in  and publicly traded on the american stock exchange with class a shares under the ticker symbol aela through the long secular bear market and economic malaise of the s the company performed well leading up to the early s recession when troubles began to surface in  earnings came in at us million excluding an extraordinary charge of us million however coming out of the recession by  the company suffered a loss of us million excluding extraordinary income of us million by  the company was in serious trouble the loss that year had grown to us million excluding an extradordinary charge of an additional us million that year anglo energy 